sp_scores.title: Exploit the Oilboyle's weakness to fire attacks.

tip_battle.message: Oilboyle counters attacks with Oil Blast, kupo, and that means you'll end up Blinded or Sapped! Tip the odds back in your favor by exploiting its weakness, fire!
tip_battle.title: Oilboyle

dungeons.epilogue: Balamb Garden had fallen into chaos as a struggle raged between the Garden Faculty and SeeD forces loyal to Headmaster Cid. Squall's team made it to the console in the MD Level, activating the Garden's emergency mobile mode, and the riots quieted as the Garden headed out to sea.
dungeons.name: Balamb Garden MD
dungeons.prologue: On orders from Headmaster Cid, Squall's team descends to the MD Level beneath Balamb Garden, where they must activate an emergency console to save the academy.

sp_scores.title: Exploit Diabolos's weakness to wind attacks.

tip_battle.message: Diabolos's Gravija will knock off a quarter of your remaining HP, kupo! Be sure to heal up after getting hit by that! He's vulnerable to wind attacks, so use those to finish him off fast!
tip_battle.title: Diabolos

dungeons.epilogue: When they used the magic lamp Cid had given them, the party was plunged into darkness, and Diabolos appeared before them. The battle that ensued was no easy victory, as Diabolos wielded devastating gravity attacks. Yet at last they defeated the powerful foe, and had a new Guardian Force--Diabolos himself--for their trouble.
dungeons.name: Balamb Garden 2
dungeons.prologue: Now full members of SeeD, Squall and the others receive their first deployment orders, and with them, a mysterious lamp from Headmaster Cid...

dungeons.epilogue: Laguna's squad was cornered at the top of a cliff by Esthar troops, and Kiros and Ward had been gravely wounded. Laguna hurled his men into the sea to safety, but he faltered as he prepared to jump after them and tumbled down the cliff. When Squall awoke, he found that Zell, Selphie, and Quistis had all had the same dream, but none of them knew what it meant...
dungeons.name: Centra Excavation Site
dungeons.prologue: In Squall's dream, Laguna and his squad scout the Esthar excavation site in Centra. They encounter heavier-than-expected defenses as they advance through the tunnels.

sp_scores.title: Defeat Biggs and Wedge without being KO'd.

tip_battle.message: Biggs counter attacks with Lariat when you attack him, so be ready! Once Biggs falls, Wedge joins the battle, so send him packing too, kupo!
tip_battle.title: Biggs & Wedge

sp_scores.title: Defeat Elvoret without being KO'd.

tip_battle.message: Elvoret casts powerful magic, kupo, and its Storm Breath attack hits the whole party, so watch out! Use abilities like Magic Break and Shell to weather the withering magic!
tip_battle.title: Elvoret

dungeons.epilogue: Seifer broke orders and headed for the radio tower. Amid the battle they encountered Selphie, who had been sent to deliver Seifer new orders to withdraw--but he had already run on ahead. With Selphie at their side, Squall and Zell chased after Seifer and finally reached the radio tower. After fighting Biggs and Wedge, they managed to secure the radio tower, but found they had only minutes left to reach the shore and withdraw with the rest of SeeD.
dungeons.name: SeeD Field Exam
dungeons.prologue: Squall and Zell are assigned to a three-man squad led by Seifer for their SeeD field exam. As they approach the exam site in the Duchy of Dollet, the shells whizzing overhead make it clear that they are entering a true war zone.

sp_scores.title: Defeat Biggs and Wedge without being KO'd.

tip_battle.message: Biggs casts Haste and Cure, making him one annoying guy to have around, kupo! Biggs also counters when you attack him, but it's still worth taking him down first. Trust me, kupo!
tip_battle.title: Biggs & Wedge

dungeons.epilogue: With the help of the Moombas, Zell rescued Squall from the torture chamber, but getting out of the underground D-District Prison was not so easy. The timely arrival of Rinoa and the marksman Irvine saved the day and the party escaped. Above ground, they learned of a planned missile atttack on Balamb and Trabia, and so the party split up to help.
dungeons.name: D-District Prison
dungeons.prologue: Defeated by Edea, Squall and the others are sent to the D-District Prison. Their weapons are confiscated, but Zell, skilled in unarmed combat, engineers their escape.

sp_scores.title: Exploit BGH251F2's weakness to lightning attacks.

tip_battle.message: When BGH251F2 gets low on HP it uses Beam Cannon, a powerful single-target attack! Blinding it will make the fight much easier, kupo! Then just bring it down fast with lightning, its weakness!
tip_battle.title: BGH251F2

dungeons.epilogue: Selphie's team returned, having miraculously survived the explosion of the missile base by taking shelter inside the BGH251F2 war machine. Repairs on Balamb Garden restored its mobility, and Squall took command of the moving fortress, vowing to defeat the Sorceress.
dungeons.name: Fisherman's Horizon
dungeons.prologue: Balamb Garden has crashed into Fisherman's Horizon, where Galbadian forces appear, searching for Ellone, a girl with strange powers.

sp_scores.title: Exploit the Oilboyle's weakness to fire attacks.

tip_battle.message: Oilboyle counters attacks with Oil Blast, kupo, and that means you'll end up Blinded or Sapped! Tip the odds back in your favor by exploiting its weakness, fire!
tip_battle.title: Oilboyle

dungeons.name: Balamb Garden MD
dungeons.prologue: On orders from Headmaster Cid, Squall's team descends to the MD Level beneath Balamb Garden, where they must activate an emergency console to save the academy.

sp_scores.title: Exploit Granaldo's weakness to wind attacks.

tip_battle.message: Granaldo and the Raldos have their very own Combo Attack, so take down one or the other first to keep them from using it!
tip_battle.title: Granaldo

dungeons.epilogue: The source of the scream was a lone woman being attacked by an insectoid creature, which the party eventually managed to defeat. Strangely, the woman addressed Squall and Quistis by name, though neither of them recalled ever having met her. Who could she be?
dungeons.name: Balamb Garden 1
dungeons.prologue: Having passed his final exam, Squall becomes an official member of SeeD. At the graduation party, he meets Rinoa, with whom he reluctantly agrees to dance. Quistis takes Squall aside to talk after the party, and as they head back to their quarters, they hear a woman scream.

sp_scores.title: Exploit Gerogero's weakness to fire attacks.
Exploit Gerogero's weakness to earth attacks.
Exploit Gerogero's weakness to holy attacks.

tip_battle.message: The president was a fake, kupo! Now that Gerogero has been unmasked, use its vulnerability to fire, earth, and holy to take it down! Gerogero spews all sorts of noxious afflictions on the party, so be ready to clean up with Esuna!
tip_battle.title: Gerogero

dungeons.epilogue: Squall's path again crossed with Rinoa's, a member of the Forest Owls. Together they succeeded in infiltrating the president's train, but the president was not aboard: in his place was a monster mimicking his appearance. Undeterred by the false lead, Rinoa suggested a target for their next operation.
dungeons.name: Presidential Train
dungeons.prologue: Squall and his party make their way toward Timber, site of their first assignment. Once there, they are to assist the Forest Owls resistance in abducting President Deling.

dungeons.epilogue: Selphie's team managed to stop the missiles from launching and fled after activating the base's self-destruct sequence, but the enemy moved swiftly and restarted the missile launch. The party's escape was blocked by the giant war machine BGH251F2, trapping them inside as flames engulfed the base.
dungeons.name: Missile Base
dungeons.prologue: Selphie's team infiltrates the Galbadia Missile Base in an attempt to stop the attack on Balamb Garden.

dungeons.name: Balamb Garden 1
dungeons.prologue: Having passed his final exam, Squall becomes an official member of SeeD. At the graduation party, he meets Rinoa, with whom he reluctantly agrees to dance. Quistis takes Squall aside to talk after the party, and as they head back to their quarters, they hear a woman scream.

sp_scores.title: Exploit Sekhret's weakness to poison attacks.
Exploit the Minotaur's weakness to wind attacks.

tip_battle.message: Minotaur and Sekhret are both vulnerable to wind and poison, kupo, so arm yourself with abilities like Aero Strike and Bio! They use a powerful group attack when they're together, so focus your attacks on one of them to put the kibosh on the pain!
tip_battle.title: Minotaur & Sekhret

dungeons.epilogue: Passing the soldier's test to enter Caraway's mansion proved easy enough, but deep within the labyrinthine Tomb of the Unknown King awaited a greater challenge: the brothers Minotaur and Sekhret, watchers of the tomb. Defeating them earned Squall and the others the Brothers Guardian Force. They then returned to Deling City, where a fateful mission awaited them.
dungeons.name: Unknown King's Tomb
dungeons.prologue: New orders from Headmaster Cid await Squall when the party reaches Galbadia Garden. Now they must find a way into General Caraway's mansion, which leads them to the Tomb of the Unknown King.

tip_battle.message: Attack Ifrit with his vulnerability, ice! If you attack him with fire you'll just heal him. Why would you want to do that, kupo?
tip_battle.title: Ifrit

dungeons.epilogue: Deep within the cavern, past rivers of molten rock, Squall and Quistis encountered Ifrit, the living embodiment of fire. Invoking Shiva and her powers of ice, they defeated Ifrit and obtained him as a new Guardian Force. Having qualified for the SeeD field exam, they make their way out of the sweltering cavern.
dungeons.name: Fire Cavern
dungeons.prologue: Squall has undergone rigorous training as a student at Balamb Garden Military Academy. Now, to earn a chance to become a member of SeeD, Garden's elite mercenary force, he and Quistis head for the Fire Cavern.

sp_scores.title: Exploit X-ATM092's weakness to lightning attacks.

tip_battle.message: X-ATM092 is vulnerable to lightning, so let the thunder rumble! You'll face it more than once, so keep an eye on your ability uses! Honing your lightning abilities will help keep you from running out!
tip_battle.title: X-ATM092

dungeons.epilogue: The X-ATM092 pursued Squall's squad as they made their way to the beach. The squad managed to stay just ahead of the relentless spider mech, and after a harrowing chase through the streets of Dollet they boarded the waiting landing craft, putting an end to the brutal field test. The SeeD operation in Dollet ended in success.
dungeons.name: Dollet
dungeons.prologue: Squall and his party make their way toward the beach to withdraw before their ships pull out, but Biggs has one final plan to stop them from escaping.
